This profile plug-in is not part of the SDK and appears to use classes that are no longer in the sdk. please open a bug against whoever supplies that plug-in.
It shouldn't break the Eclipse configuration manager though. If you look at the Stack trace it is trying to use the eclipse core.

that's not what's happening.  

The profiler plug-in you downloaded is not compatible with the Eclipse version you are running.

The profiler binary code is trying to call an old internal PDE class that was removed in the Eclipse version you are running and is getting a noclassdeffound error as a result.
